<br>
Personally, I think being strong in your faith is wonderful. No matter what I believe, everyone has the right to believe what they need to believe (Who knows... maybe your belief is 100% correct. I am not one to say you are wrong) What I do not agree with is the different sects of the same religion telling the other sects they are &quot;going to hell&quot; because of a doctrinal difference. It just blows my mind.<br>
<br>
My mother (whose mission in life is to convert all the world to Christianity before she dies) has told us that we are going to hell because we think Paul was a false prophet. ~ Then we had a sermon preached about a conversation we had with the asst pastor about the same subject (with the same message... anyone who does not believe everything 100% in the bible is going to hell). That was the last time I sat through a christian church service.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I do not feel that anyone has a right to judge how you worship. If G-d exists, then it is no one's business except yours and his.<br>
